    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab><persName ref="#people/3317">Firmo</persName> filio <persName
                            ref="#people/3316">bone memorie Gumperti</persName> permuta beni con
                            <persName ref="#people/214" key="#Bishops">Gherardus</persName> gratia
                        Dei huius Sancte <placeName ref="#places/4"
                            key="#Churches #Mother_churches #Bishops">Lucane</placeName> ecclesie
                        humilis <rs key="#Bishops">episcopus</rs> (…). (…). Firmo cede a Gherardo ad
                        pars <rs key="#Churches">ecclesie</rs>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/294" key="#Churches">Sancti
                            Donati</orgName>, que est de suppotestatem ipsius <rs
                            key="#Mother_churches">episcopatui</rs> vestri <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/68" key="#Mother_churches">Sancti
                            Martini</orgName>, id est <rs key="#Wine">vinee</rs> mee ille, quam abeo
                        in loco ubi dicitur <placeName ref="#places/3338" key="#Confinia #Wine"
                            >Saliscamo</placeName> et sunt in simul <rs key="#Confinia">tenentes
                            ipse vinee capo uno cum uno lato</rs> in <rs key="#Wine">vinea</rs> qui
                        fuit <persName key="#Confinia #Wine" ref="#people/211">quondam
                            Teudimundi</persName>, alio capo tenet in <rs key="#Wine">vinea</rs>,
                        qui fuit <persName key="#Confinia #Wine">quondam <name ref="Gregorius"
                                >Gregorii</name></persName>, alio lato in <rs key="#Wine">vinea</rs>
                        <persName key="#Confinia #Wine #Priests"><name ref="Natalis"
                            >Natali</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbiteri</rs>; simul et (…) <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">terra</rs> mea illa, ubi dicitur <placeName
                            ref="#places/22" key="#Confinia #Rivers #Landed_possessions">ad Noghare,
                            prope Flexo</placeName>, qui <rs key="#Confinia">capo uno tene</rs> in
                            <rs key="#Rivers">fluvio Ausere</rs>, et alio capo tene in <rs
                            key="#Roads">via publica</rs>, lato uno tene in <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">terra</rs>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/68" key="#Confinia #Landed_possessions"
                            >Sancti Martini</orgName>, alio lato tene in <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">terra</rs> qui fuit <persName>quondam <name
                                ref="Peredeo">Peritei</name></persName>; has predicte vinee sicut
                        prefata terra (…) sunt per mensura ad iusta perticha mensurata <rs
                            key="#Size">modiorum duo et sistariorum undecim</rs>, una cum cesis et
                        arboribus suis (…). Riceve in cambio ad pars suprascripte ecclesie Sancti
                        Donati (…) una <rs key="#Petiae #Landed_possessions #Hay/fodder">petia de
                            terra illa quot est prato</rs>
                        <placeName ref="#places/4"
                            key="#Cities #Confinia #Petiae #Landed_possessions #Hay/fodder #Fiscal_property #Mention #Countess"
                            >foras <rs key="#Cities">civitate</rs> ista Lucense, prope <rs
                                key="#Churches">ecclesie</rs>
                            <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/294" key="#Churches">Sancti
                                Donati</orgName></placeName>, pertinens ipsius ecclesie, qui est de
                        suppotestate ipsius episcopatus vestri Sancti Martini, et <rs
                            key="#Confinia">est tenentes</rs> ipse terra capo uno cum ambas latera
                        in <rs key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Mention #Countess">terra
                                <persName
                                key="#Confinia #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Mention #Countess #marriage"
                                ref="#people/3312">Rottilde</persName> comitissa</rs>, <rs
                            key="#marriage">coniux</rs>
                        <persName ref="#people/1514" key="#Count #marriage">Adalberti</persName>
                        <rs key="#Count">comes</rs>, alio lato tene in <rs key="#Landed_possessions"
                            >terra</rs> ipsius <rs key="#Churches">ecclesie</rs> vestre <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/294" key="#Churches">Sancti Donati</orgName>,
                        quas mihi menime dedisti, quomodo signa posite sunt; petia ipsa de terra
                        quot est prato (…) est per mensura ad insta perticha mensurata <rs
                            key="#Size">modiorum unum et sistariorum quattuor</rs> (…) una cum cesis
                        et sepi et omnibus arboribus suis (…). Ubi et super hanc comutationem tu qui
                        supra <persName ref="#people/214"
                            key="#Missus_of_other_public_authorities #Bishops">Gherardus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopus</rs> direxisti <rs
                            key="#Missus_of_other_public_authorities">missos tuos</rs>, i sunt
                            <persName key="#Missus_of_other_public_authorities #Priests"
                            ref="#people/3318">Ardimanno</persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbitero</rs> et <persName
                            key="#Missus_of_other_public_authorities #Deacons"><name
                                ref="Sigelfredus">Sichalfridi </name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Deacons">diaconus</rs> seo <persName
                            key="#Missus_of_other_public_authorities"><name ref="Ermiteus"
                                >Ermiteo</name></persName>, et <persName ref="#people/1514"
                            key="#Marquis/duke #Missus_of_other_public_authorities"
                            >Adalbertus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Marquis/duke">dux</rs> direxit <rs
                            key="#Missus_of_other_public_authorities">missos suos</rs>, i sunt
                            <persName key="#Notary #Missus_of_other_public_authorities #Scabini"
                                ><name ref="Adalfredus">Adalfridi</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs> et <rs key="#Scabini">scabinus</rs> et
                            <persName key="#Missus_of_other_public_authorities"><name
                                ref="Adroaldus">Atrualdo</name></persName> seo <persName
                            key="#Missus_of_other_public_authorities"><name ref="Deusdedit"
                                >Deusdedi</name></persName>, qui ambulaverunt (…). […] </ab>
                    <ab>La pergamena è mutila nella parte inferiore e non è possibile leggere le
                        sottoscrizioni. In base all’analisi della scrittura è possibile riconoscere
                        in <persName key="#Writer #Notary"><name ref="Rofredus"
                            >Roffridi</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs> l’<rs key="#Writer">estensore materiale</rs>
                        del documento.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
